<h1>E-Commerce Operations Automation:<br />Why It's Become Unavoidable</h1>

<p>In e-commerce companies, <strong>60% of customer service queries are order status questions</strong>. For a company processing 500 orders a day, that means the customer service team answers 300 questions daily. A large portion of those 300 questions could be eliminated entirely with automatic notifications.</p>

<h2>The 5 Biggest Time Wasters in Retail</h2>

<h3>1. Order status notifications</h3>
<p>Customers want to know where their order is. Not delivering this information systematically multiplies the customer service workload.</p>

<h3>2. Multi-platform inventory management</h3>
<p>Website, Trendyol, Hepsiburada, physical store — separate inventory tracking in each. Update delays lead to overselling, cancellations, and customer disappointment.</p>

<h3>3. Return process management</h3>
<p>Return requests turn into email chains, tracking numbers are manually created, and stock re-entry is done manually. Each return transaction takes an average of 15–20 minutes.</p>

<h3>4. Sales reporting</h3>
<p>Pulling data from different channels, combining it, and analyzing it takes hours. Accurate data arrives late, causing decision delays.</p>

<h3>5. Supplier orders</h3>
<p>When stock hits a critical level, a supplier order is manually placed. Automatic replenishment triggers eliminate this step.</p>

